The paper discusses text summarization using neural models, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of machine learning models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The evaluation metrics and datasets used in the paper suggest that it could also belong to cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the paper discusses the limitations of current models, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
